quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  32,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  32,2,"The bestowal of the Scripture from on high is—no doubt about it—by the Lord of all realms."
  32,3,"Yet they say, “He has fabricated it.” Rather, it is the truth from yoursg Lord, so that you may warn a people to whom no warner came before you, that they may be guided."
  32,4,"Allah is the One Who created the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them in six days{1}, and then settled over the Throne; apart from Him, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have neither ally nor intercessor. Will you not remind yourselves?",footnotes:1:Six equal intervals of time, which may be six heavenly days, each of them being 1000 earthly years long (see 22: 47).
  32,5,"He governs every matter from the heavens to the earth, then it ascends to Him on a day the length of which is a thousand years by yourpl count."
  32,6,"That is the Knower of the hidden realm and the manifest, the Almighty, the Bestower of mercy"
  32,7,"Who has made <span class=",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Nafie’, Asem, Hamza, Al-Kesa’i and Khalaf read it as: “…Who has made everything excellent regarding its composition, and He…”</span>
  32,8,"then made his progeny from an extract of a despicable fluid,"
  32,9,"then He proportioned him and breathed into him of His Spirit, and He gave youpl hearing and sight(s) and burning hearts; little do you give thanks."
  32,10,"And they said, “<span class=""h"">Can it be that</span>when we have becomelost into the earth—<span class=""h"">can it be that</span>we will{1}reallybe brought to a new creation?” Rather, they do deny the meeting with their Lord.",footnotes:1:<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Nafie’, Al-Kesa’i and Ya’qub read it as: “Can it be that when we have become lost into the earth we will really…” Ibn Amer and Abu Ja’far read it as: “When we have become lost into the earth— can it be that we will really …”</span>